name: Bilibin style illustrations (Иван Билибин)
description:
Recommended weight: 1

v1 trained on AoM3 and look oversaturated on most models.

v2 retrained on Anythingv3 and generates slightly subdued colors

Generates pictures in the style of children's books

Bilibin’s book illustration is usually characterised by lively visual references to Russian history and folk art. The tones he favoured in his illustrations of Russian fairy and traditional tales hint at the bright and glorious, yet they are strangely muted; even in open vistas, the light might be have been filtered through a thick forest canopy.

modelVersions.name: AoM3
modelVersions.description:
Trained on AoM3A1, 16/20 epochs.

Fine with AoM based models, oversaturated on other models including Any3.

This version can generate frames and book spreads, but they look stylish and usually don't mess up the image. It can also generate text captions.

No manual tagging because of gradio update
